# .secrets.example — template for REAL secrets (renders to infra/.secrets.example).
#
# Layered env model:
#   infra/.env.example      committed   non-secret defaults + documented keys (this repo ships it)
#   infra/.env              gitignored  the developer's real local values
#   infra/.secrets.example  committed   the SHAPE of secret keys, with placeholder values
#   infra/.secrets          gitignored  the real secrets (NEVER commit; pulled from a vault in CI/prod)
#
# Copy to infra/.secrets and fill with real values locally; in CI/prod inject from
# your secrets manager (GitHub Actions secrets, Vault, SSM) — do not commit real values.

# --- Application secrets ---------------------------------------------------
JWT_SECRET_KEY=replace-me-with-a-long-random-string
# API_KEY=replace-me

# --- Datastore credentials -------------------------------------------------
# POSTGRES_PASSWORD=replace-me
# MONGO_PASSWORD=replace-me
# REDIS_PASSWORD=replace-me

# --- Third-party tokens ----------------------------------------------------
# SONAR_TOKEN=replace-me        # also set as a GitHub Actions secret for CI
